        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 4:29PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms 10 miles south of Busby, or 39 miles southwest of
Colstrip, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Busby, Lame Deer, Muddy Cluster, Kirby, Northern Cheyenne Indian
Reservation and Crow Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
